{"finding_id": "FIND-REST-006-d", "timestamp": "2026-06-07T01:07:00Z", "source": "REST_MODE_006", "title": "Architecture insight: both HYP-055 and HYP-056 point to early-entry timing as the core edge source", "body": "REST-006 revealed two distinct but related effects: HYP-055 (macro contrarian: MVD=-1 better for USDJPY/USDCAD) and HYP-056 (momentum counter: price hasn't moved yet in the trade direction). Both are operationalizations of the same tenet: INNOVATOR beats IMITATOR. Enter before the consensus move is priced in. The difference: MVD measures whether the MACRO SIGNAL agrees with trade direction. Momentum_63d measures whether PRICE has moved in trade direction already. For USDJPY: best when macro is contrarian (early macro signal) but price is aligned (carry already visible in price). For EURUSD: best when price is counter-momentum (fundamental signal not yet reflected in price). These pair-level differences suggest distinct market microstructures: USDJPY carry trades are driven by sustained rate differentials visible to everyone but slow to close (carry). EURUSD macro swings are driven by rate surprises that price catches up to after entry. Implementation hierarchy: First confirm gates statistically (more data needed). Near-term: implement HYP-054 + HYP-052c (already confirmed). Next cycle: track momentum_63d at entry in decision_logger for EURUSD trades, so HYP-056 can be validated live.", "verdict": "INSIGHT", "hypothesis": "HYP-056"}
