{"finding_id": "FIND-REST-015-a", "timestamp": "2026-06-12T01:15:00Z", "source": "REST_MODE_011", "hypothesis_id": "HYP-053", "title": "Rate-spread |velocity| size gate REJECTED on canonical costed v003 log \u2014 reduces portfolio Sharpe at every causal lookback and even under look-ahead", "body": "RQ-REST-011 ran the proposed 90d rolling rate-spread |velocity| position-size throttle (velocity>p50->1.0x, p25-p50->0.5x, <p25->0.25x) over the canonical v003 4-pair costed log (n=276 trades, 2015-2022; baseline portfolio Sharpe 0.6702 reproduced exactly from v003 metadata). PRIMARY causal |vel| 90d: gated Sharpe 0.6354 (dSharpe -0.035), maxDD unchanged -0.0967. 60d -0.028, 120d -0.030 \u2014 every causal lookback is NEGATIVE. The full-sample LOOK-AHEAD variant (which is allowed to cheat) is still -0.0096, so there is no recoverable benefit even with hindsight. Mechanism: the premise 'low velocity = bad year' is FALSE on this log \u2014 2020 (mult 0.55) and 2021 (mult 0.44, base Sharpe 2.79) were LOW-velocity GOOD years, so the gate throttles winners. This independently confirms and extends FIND-REST-014-b (overlay 'costs sumR, variance-only' on the entry log). NOTE: canonical log ends 2022, so the RQ's '2024 material improvement' claim is untestable here; the 2021 claim IS testable and FAILS. The original 'predicts 3/4 bad years' signal was on the smaller v014 n=119 log and does not replicate. Do NOT wire as a live size gate.", "verdict": "REJECTED", "artifact": "data/research/rq_rest_011_velocity_size_gate_results.json"}
